====<span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; font-size: 14pt;">Hence, Kushal and I advocate that United States Federal Government should substantially increase its investment in transportation infrastructure in the United States. </span>==== 
====<span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; font-size: 14pt;">We choose to interrogate the resolution and affirm the abject by confronting and embracing the liminal spaces intrinsic to the resolution. We advocate a holistic investment in transportation infrastructure because the liminal spaces we have isolated are abjects and we choose to dismantle the constant process of abjection by affirming those abjects. We will holistically defend these spaces and transportation infrastructure however we do not defend fiat and will not defend against disads premised on fiat.</span>==== 


**<span style="font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; font-size: 14pt;">Our argument is simple. There are abjects in the resolution that are avoided. These are what we claim are liminal spaces, that is the road, the airport, and urban/suburban infrastructure. The road is a liminal space in terms of identity because the subject can take on a hybrid identity of adult and child in which their existence is multiple yet non-existent. The airport is a liminal space because it is the intermediary zone between destinations in which anxiety is amplified by waiting. This is where our understanding of anxiety is heightened and we therefore try to avoid thinking about it. The urban/suburban infrastructure is liminal because they correspond to the masculine-feminine dichotomy and the person traveling between the two therefore is affected abjectly in the context of this infrastructure. Our argument is that abjection, or the process of casting out because something is disturbing, is bad because we are trapped in a constant attempt to rid the world of these abjects. However, the abject is an inevitable condition of life and the gap between the fantasy we aim for and the reality creates a feeling of dejection within us in which we can't experience the organic enjoyment of life. So, to stop this form of dejection and abjection, we say to affirm the abjects in the resolution.</span>**
